node.text:
When I started @Elaluz I always knew the brand would go beyond beauty. The name Elaluz means she is light and we're excited to kick off our most important brand pillar to celebrate and support those spreading light in our communities. During this challenging time we feel so grateful for our front line medical workers. This past week we stopped by our local hospital, Cedars-Sinai Los Angeles, to share some of our EWG VERIFIED™️ products and show them our support! 

If you know someone in your community who is spreading light, we want to spotlight them! Whether it's our healthcare workers on the front lines or picking up groceries for a neighbor, everyday people are lifting up their communities and we want to share their stories. Drop into our DMs if there's someone you want to spotlight, and look out for more information from us on how to nominate someone—coming soon✨

To learn more about how you can support your frontline medical community through organizations like @wckitchen and @flexport, head to elaluz.com for a list of ways to get involved. Thanks and keep spreading the light!✨✨

P.S.— special thanks to @revolve for joining us in this effort and donating 5k masks! 

#stepintothelight 
#spreadthelight

node.text:
I never thought I would be so deeply open about my personal life. (If you watch my stories you see me going deeper into personal things, and challenges, including epilepsy) but to share all the details on what has made me the most vulnerable throughout the years in one video feels a bit scary. My hope is that by sharing my story, my struggles and challenges, I can hopefully inspire those who are struggling right now, especially with accepting and loving themselves! 🙏 (learn more about Epilepsy at @epilepsyfdn ) 
————-

Nunca pensei que seria tão profundamente aberta sobre minha vida pessoal. (Se você assiste meus stories, sabe que compartilho  mais a fundo coisas pessoais, e desafios que tenho, incluindo epilepsia) Mas compartilhar todos os detalhes sobre o que me tornou mais vulnerável ao longo dos anos, em um vídeo, é um pouco assustador. Minha esperança é que compartilhando minha história, minhas lutas e desafios, eu possa ajudar aqueles que estão lutando agora, especialmente com aceitação própria e amando a si mesmos!
